.HL 2 ^*IMP TESTING PROCEDURE\*

^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*

.HL 3 ^*INTRODUCTION\*

.P 0;This document briefly describes the testing procedure that will be used on 
each of the modules in the IMP (IFF Map Processing) package. Each module must 
be shown to work successfully on:
.LIST 
.LE;Existing 'old' type IFF files,
.LE;'New' type IFF files with HI (HIstory), new type 2 MD (Map Descriptor), 
ZS (3 dimensional strings) and TS (Text Status) entries. 
.LE;A mixture of 'old' and 'new' files (where applicable).
.END LIST 


.HL 3 ^*INDIVIDUAL MODULES\*

.P 0;Individual modules will be exercised so that every qualifier is checked
against documented behaviour for both 'old' and 'new' type IFF files. Those
modules that operate on more than one file (IDIFFERENCE and IMERGE) will also
be exercised on a mixture of 'old' and 'new' type files. 

.BLANK
.HL 4 ^*Documentation\*

.P 0;The module User-Guide, User-Reference-Manual and On-line help will be 
checked for correspondence. All documented examples will be validated. 
.BLANK
.HL 4 ^*File structure\*

.P 0;Output IFF files will be checked for validity. IFF entries will be checked 
for correct order within specified levels (see IFFLIB documentation) and correct
correspondence (NO, EO pointers). FS and TS entries will be checked for correct
setting of relevant bits.

.BLANK
.HL 4 ^*Program execution\*
.P 0;Program execution will be checked against documented behaviour. Program
messages and the correct setting of $STATUS will be checked.

.BLANK
.HL 3 ^*PACKAGE TESTING\*

.P 0;The package will be checked for internal consistancy in documentation
and error messages. Sample flowlines will be set up to check consistancy
of the whole package for 'old' and 'new' type IFF files for:
.LIST 
.LE;LSL type files
.LE;OS type files
.LE;MCE type files
.END LIST 

.BLANK
